{{Quote|In the deep state of Rising Meditation, Jedi may find their sense of the Force increases and that their bodies rise from the ground.|[[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Skarch Vaunk]]|<ref name="The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)">[[The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force (real-life book)|''The Jedi Path: A Manual for Students of the Force'']]</ref>}}
'''Floating Meditation''', also known as '''Rising Meditation''', was a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] meditation technique where one meditated while using [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to float several inches off the ground. Often, surrounding objects would revolve around the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]]. Sometimes someone used [[Battle meditation/Legends|Battle Meditation]] would perform this act at the same time.<ref name="Heir to the Empire 2">[[Heir to the Empire 2|''Heir to the Empire'' 2]]</ref>

This technique was used by [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] when he was being re-trained at the [[Jedi Enclave]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]], where he floated himself, and several objects (chairs and a [[Datapad/Legends|datapad]]) during meditation. [[Bastila Shan]] would use this power during her [[Battle meditation/Legends|Battle meditation]]. [[Barriss Offee/Legends|Barriss Offee]] also used this technique often. [[Galen Marek]] used this meditation in order to find [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]]. [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] accidentally discovered this technique years ago when he was roused by Han Solo and found that he was a meter off the ground. He also used this technique while being imprisoned by the [[Joiner]]s on [[Woteba]]. [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] meditated this way, believing that contact with the ground could prove distracting.

